  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: If send message that takes 3 or more lines then input field has height of 3 lines instead of 1. If use @browse command in such field then command and hint are misaligned\r\n![android 3 lines](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/26061331/e93f30b6-3987-11e7-9777-5c879d163521.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nAfter text is sent, input field takes 1 line\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nAfter text is sent, input field takes 3 lines\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nVideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7a1NPTXo4cFFacHc\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open cosnole\r\n- Type 1 press Enter, tap 2 press Enter, tap 3 press enter\r\n- Send message\r\n- Check the height of the input field\r\n- tap on @browse command check how it's aligned with hint URL (the issue with misalignment happens on Android only) \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.7\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS",
